description:
&lt;p&gt;There are 4 case managers posts across the iCares Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Care homes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Admission avoidance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Locality long term conditions management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Discharge 2 Assess &amp; Virtual Ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for nurses who are passionate about people. You must have a vision for community nursing, the energy to support your patients in their community and a focus on outstanding quality and safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts sit within the iCares Directorate which is expanding due to investment. The community nurses are integral to integrated pathways and improving health outcomes for our population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are particularly interested in applications from District Nurses as we integrate the iCares Service with the District Nursing team and develop the DN case management role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full induction, support and training is available for all the posts in the Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time posts will be welcomed, as long as you can support the service across the 7 day working pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to support you in a development post if you are looking to move from a band 5 to a band 6 post but not quite ready yet. Please make this clear on your application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRuth WilliamsJob titleClinical Directorate LeadEmail addresssandwell.icares@nhs.netTelephone number0121 507 2664 (option 5)&lt;/p&gt;
